hydrogen, and sulfur.

4
00:00:11,059 --> 00:00:15,009
Inside the boiler’s combustion chamber,
these elements react with oxygen and nitrogen

5
00:00:15,009 --> 00:00:18,760
from the supplied air to
generate heat and form carbon dioxide, nitrogen

6
00:00:18,760 --> 00:00:22,430
oxides, sulfur dioxides, and water vapor.

7
00:00:22,430 --> 00:00:26,949
Two types of fuel sources are used at the
Central Heating Plant: natural gas and low-sulfur

8
00:00:26,949 --> 00:00:28,590
diesel fuel oil.

9
00:00:28,590 --> 00:00:33,520
Natural gas emits about 28% less carbon dioxide
and three times less nitrogen oxides than

10
00:00:33,520 --> 00:00:34,590
fuel oil.

11
00:00:34,590 --> 00:00:39,130
The Plant uses natural gas as the primary
fuel to reduce campus pollution emissions,

12
00:00:39,130 --> 00:00:41,710
operations,
and maintenance costs.

13
00:00:41,710 --> 00:00:47,110
