The quantity of heat generated by the complete
combustion of a unit of a specific fuel is

24
00:01:32,119 --> 00:01:37,119
constant and is termed the “heating value”
or “heat of combustion” of that fuel.

25
00:01:37,119 --> 00:01:41,270
The efficiency of a boiler that involves the
combustion of a fuel is based on the heating

26
00:01:41,270 --> 00:01:45,689
value of the fuel, which is the amount of
heat released when a unit amount of fuel at

27
00:01:45,689 --> 00:01:49,500
room temperature is completely burned and
the combustion products are cooled to the

28
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:50,500
room temperature.

29
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:55,840
Then, the boiler performance can be characterized
by combustion efficiency as seen in the formulas

30
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:59,250
